[SN]TITLE[SN]
Brighton coach crash: Girl, 6, seriously injured

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A six-year-old girl has been seriously injured after being hit by a coach carrying children on a school trip.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The child and her mother were both struck in the collision in Marlborough Place, Brighton, close to the King and Queen pub, at about 09:00 BST.
The girl was taken to hospital by air ambulance, while her mother sustained minor injuries, Sussex Police said.
No-one on the coach was injured. A section of the road was closed for investigations, officers said.
